In December, the U.N. said around one million Syrians have registered as refugees in
neighboring Turkey, Jordan, Lebanon, Iraq and Egypt since the uprising against President Bashir Assad began two years ago.

Since December the exodus has picked up, with some 7,000 fleeing Syria every day.

Several 
hundred thousand more have fled the country but haven't signed up with the 
U.N. refugee agency.

Most are living in camps. Zaatari, one of Jordan's largest, is home to some 120,000 people.

