Refugees have been struggling with 
harsh desert conditions, including cold and floods in the winter, and 
scorching heat, along with snakes and scorpions, in the summer.

in December, several dozen refugees rioted 
in Zaatari early, destroying 
tents and medicine and leaving scores of refugee families out in the 
night cold.

Jordanian men also are moving the 
other way across the border - joining what intelligence officials have 
estimated to be around 2,000 foreigners fighting alongside Syrian rebels
trying to topple Assad.

